x4freetext: 3 MV pulsed Van De Graaff, IBIS, giving
pulses of less than 1 nanosecond at a
3 MeV deuterons incident on a 1.5 cm gas
Natural elements in the form of hollow right
cylinders suspended by thin iron wires at 0 degrees
to the beam, 10.5 cm from the centre of the gas cell.
Neutron yield from gas cell was monitored by two
independent TOF systems, in which the time peaks due
to neutrons from H-2(d,n) reaction were electronically
selected and counted.These monitor detectors were
placed at 20 deg and 35 deg with flight path about 6m.
and 2.54 cm thick, coupled to an XP1040 photo-
Detector biased at 60 keV gamma ray of Am-241.
Energy dependence of detector efficiency was
determined by known angular dependence of H-2(d,n)
cross section and measured counting rates in detector.
Li(p,n),H-3(p,n) reactions were used at lower energies
Same detector placed at 0 degrees to measure
direct neutron flux. Flight path increased to
7 m and deuterium gas pressure reduced to 0.5
Atmospheres to reduce the count rate.
Areas under various peaks in TOF spectra were
Integrated counts in peaks at different angles were
internally normalized to the sum of two monitor
yields.Resulting raw angular distributions were then
normalized absolutely, corrected and transformed in
Absolute normalization from measurement at o degrees.
Alternative method of normalizing to the known c-s of
hydrogen was found to be unreliable due to degradation
of neutron energy, which resulted in even the smallest
samples of polythene compatible with a statistically
added. Corrections for 4-digits year dates and
Preliminary corrections for flux attenuation on basis
Corrections for effects of multiple scattering, flux
attenuation and anisotropy, and the finite dimensions
of the samples were made using Monte-Carlo Program
Elastic cross-sections corrected for the shape of the
Correction for effects of flux attenuation - 12%,
for shape - 15% at minima of elastic scattering
Main contributions to the total error are from the
positioning of samples and application of correction
to be about 15 % for Si, 7 % for all other  cases.
